Author: hellcatz#5825
Content: @SHossain Yes, that is my pool address. We are following consensus on block times. It may look at little funny on the explorer, as they do not show the timestamp of when the block actually arrived, but the timestamp that was included in the block.

Author: hellcatz#5825
Content: The timestamp that is included in the block is allowed to vary by 7200 seconds (zcash forks).  *update (~8 minutes for KMD)

Author: hellcatz#5825
Content:
We are following consensus and not performing any kind of attacks.  If we were, we would be orphaning blocks and not validating them.
I guess it just `looks`  really funny on the explorers.

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: komodo consensus does not allow a 7200 second variance

Author: jl777c#5810
Content: more like 8 minutes

Author: hellcatz#5825
Content: The time value being used it being provided by the daemon in `getblocktemplate`

Author: Andy#1801
Content: Hey guys. I have a question regarding assetchains. I took a brief look at the documentation and the technical explanations of how to set one up are pretty straight forward. But my question is more related to how we can interact with those asset chains from a wallet perspective. Are there docs/examples of how to do that? (Getting a list of chains, how to prepare/sign transactions for those chains, etc).

Author: jorian#4555
Content: getting a list of chains is impossible, since chains are not connected to anything. every assetchain is a blockchain on itself

Author: jorian#4555
Content: you can only list the chains you know of

Author: jorian#4555
Content: interacting with a chain is done using RPC mostly

Author: jorian#4555
Content: `komodo-cli -ac_name=<name_of_chain> createrawtransaction` for example prepares a transaction

Author: jorian#4555
Content: `komodo-cli -ac_name<name> help` lists all available commands

Author: Andy#1801
Content: Does the node also have an API that is accessible over HTTP?

Author: Andy#1801
Content: So does that mean you have to connect to a different node for each asset chain? (I assume that because it's not possible to get a list of chains).

Author: jorian#4555
Content: every assetchain comes with its own rpc port
